cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper is about video prediction, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of a neural network to predict future frames, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of a mask to outline the predicted foreground object, which is related to robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on the Human 3.6M dataset, which is a dataset commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
